{"name": "polodb-python", "metadata": {"name": "polodb-python", "version": "0.1.16", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy", "Programming Language :: Rust"], "home_page": "https://github.com/PoloDB/polodb-python", "license": "Apache License", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["tomli"], "summary": "Add your description here", "upload_time": 1732833994}, "documentation": ["# Py-PoloDB Python Bindings\n\n## Overview\nThis repository contains the Python bindings for the [PoloDB](https://www.polodb.org) project. These bindings allow Python code to interface seamlessly with the PoloDB core functionalities written in Rust.\n\n## Installation \n```bash\npython3.9 -m pip install polodb-python\n```\n\n## Usage : \n```python\n>>> from polodb import PoloDB \n>>> db  = PoloDB(\"db\")\n>>> db\n<polodb.core.PoloDB object at 0x1001d6a00>\n>>> col = db.collection('my-collection')\n>>> col\n<polodb.core.Collection object at 0x100244d00>\n>>> data = [{\"foo\":\"bar\", \"titi\":\"kpkp\"}, {\"lol\":\"out\", \"foo\":\"bar\"}]\n>>> col.insert_many(data)\n{0: '6725102e0c6d6f91b9df53bd', 1: '6725102e0c6d6f91b9df53be'}\n>>> col.len()\n2\n>>> col.find({\"lol\":\"out\"})\n[{'lol': 'out', 'foo': 'bar', '_id': '6725102e0c6d6f91b9df53be'}]\n```\n\n### Current methods supported for collection\n\n- [x] delete_one\n- [x] delete_many\n- [x] find\n- [x] find_one\n- [x] insert_many\n- [x] insert_one\n- [x] len\n- [x] name\n- [x] update_many (with upsert option)\n- [x] update_one (with upsert option)\n- [x] aggregate\n"], "modules": [{"name": "polodb", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "polodb.__version__", "xref": {"fqname": "polodb.version.__version__", "project": null}}, {"name": "polodb.Collection", "xref": {"fqname": "polodb.core.Collection", "project": null}}, {"name": "polodb.PoloDB", "xref": {"fqname": "polodb.core.PoloDB", "project